<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Rime Editor - Visual Data Pipeline Workbench</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Rime Editor is a desktop workbench for visually authoring, running, inspecting, and reporting on Rime data pipelines."
    />
    <link rel="icon" href="data:," />
    <style>
      :root {
        color-scheme: light;
        --ink: #0a0e13;
        --ink-2: #171922;
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --paper-2: #f8fafc;
        --paper-3: #f1f5f9;
        --muted: #4a5568;
        --muted-2: #718096;
        --line: #e2e8f0;
        --line-strong: #cbd5e0;
        --accent: #0891b2;
        --accent-strong: #0e7490;
        --accent-soft: #cffafe;
        --success: #16a34a;
        --warning: #d97706;
        --danger: #dc2626;
        --shadow: 0 24px 80px rgb(10 12 18 / 22%);
        font-family:
          Inter,
          ui-sans-serif,
          system-ui,
          -apple-system,
          BlinkMacSystemFont,
          'Segoe UI',
          sans-serif;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      html {
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
      }

      a {
        color: inherit;
      }

      img {
        display: block;
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      .site-nav {
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        z-index: 20;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 24px;
        min-height: 64px;
        padding: 12px clamp(18px, 4vw, 56px);
        color: #f7f8fb;
        background: rgb(13 14 18 / 92%);
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(255 255 255 / 12%);
        backdrop-filter: blur(18px);
      }

      .brand {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: baseline;
        gap: 7px;
        font-weight: 760;
        letter-spacing: 0;
        text-decoration: none;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .brand-word {
        font-size: 22px;
        font-weight: 860;
      }

      .brand-product {
        color: rgb(255 255 255 / 68%);
        font-size: 15px;
        font-weight: 680;
      }

      .nav-links {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: flex-end;
        gap: 8px 20px;
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 680;
      }

      .nav-links a {
        color: rgb(255 255 255 / 78%);
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      .nav-links a:hover {
        color: #ffffff;
      }

      .nav-cta {
        padding: 8px 13px;
        color: #ffffff !important;
        background: var(--accent);
        border-radius: 6px;
      }

      .hero {
        position: relative;
        min-height: min(860px, 86vh);
        display: grid;
        align-items: end;
        overflow: hidden;
        color: #ffffff;
        background:
          linear-gradient(
            90deg,
            rgb(7 8 12 / 96%) 0%,
            rgb(7 8 12 / 78%) 46%,
            rgb(7 8 12 / 28%) 100%
          ),
          linear-gradient(180deg, rgb(7 8 12 / 5%) 0%, rgb(7 8 12 / 80%) 100%),
          var(--hero-image) center / cover no-repeat;
      }

      .hero::after {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        inset: auto 0 0;
        height: 18vh;
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgb(7 8 12 / 0%), rgb(13 14 18));
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      .hero-content {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
        width: min(1180px, 100%);
        padding: 96px clamp(20px, 5vw, 72px) 64px;
      }

      .product-kicker {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 8px;
        align-items: center;
        width: fit-content;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
        color: rgb(255 255 255 / 74%);
        font-size: 13px;
        font-weight: 760;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .product-kicker::before {
        content: '';
        display: inline-block;
        width: 7px;
        height: 7px;
        background: var(--accent);
      }

      h1 {
        max-width: 820px;
        margin: 0;
        font-size: clamp(58px, 12vw, 156px);
        line-height: 0.86;
        letter-spacing: 0;
      }

      .hero-copy {
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 28px 0 0;
        color: rgb(255 255 255 / 82%);
        font-size: clamp(19px, 2.2vw, 28px);
        line-height: 1.28;
      }

      .hero-actions {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 12px;
        margin-top: 34px;
      }

      .button {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 10px;
        min-height: 46px;
        padding: 12px 18px;
        border: 1px solid rgb(255 255 255 / 30%);
        border-radius: 6px;
        color: #ffffff;
        font-weight: 760;
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      .button.primary {
        color: #ffffff;
        background: var(--accent);
        border-color: var(--accent);
      }

      .button:hover {
        transform: translateY(-1px);
      }

      .button.primary:hover,
      .nav-cta:hover {
        background: var(--accent-strong);
      }

      .hero-metrics {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(130px, 1fr));
        gap: 1px;
        max-width: 760px;
        margin-top: 56px;
        background: rgb(255 255 255 / 18%);
        border: 1px solid rgb(255 255 255 / 18%);
      }

      .metric {
        padding: 18px;
        background: rgb(13 14 18 / 72%);
      }

      .metric strong {
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 5px;
        font-size: 22px;
      }

      .metric span {
        color: rgb(255 255 255 / 68%);
        font-size: 13px;
      }

      .section {
        padding: 86px clamp(20px, 5vw, 72px);
      }

      .section.dark {
        color: #ffffff;
        background: var(--ink);
      }

      .section.tight {
        padding-top: 58px;
      }

      .section-inner {
        width: min(1180px, 100%);
        margin: 0 auto;
      }

      .section-heading {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.8fr) minmax(260px, 0.55fr);
        gap: 42px;
        align-items: end;
        margin-bottom: 42px;
      }

      h2 {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: clamp(34px, 5vw, 72px);
        line-height: 0.98;
        letter-spacing: 0;
      }

      .lede {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.48;
      }

      .dark .lede {
        color: rgb(255 255 255 / 68%);
      }

      .feature-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
        gap: 16px;
      }

      .feature {
        min-height: 250px;
        padding: 26px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: 8px;
        background: #ffffff;
      }

      .feature:nth-child(2) {
        background: #f8fafc;
      }

      .feature:nth-child(3) {
        background: #fffbeb;
      }

      .feature-topline {
        width: 52px;
        height: 7px;
        margin-bottom: 28px;
        background: var(--accent);
      }

      .feature:nth-child(2) .feature-topline {
        background: var(--success);
      }

      .feature:nth-child(3) .feature-topline {
        background: var(--warning);
      }

      .feature h3,
      .guide h3,
      .example-card h3 {
        margin: 0 0 12px;
        font-size: 22px;
        line-height: 1.12;
      }

      .feature p,
      .guide p,
      .example-card p {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      .screen-wall {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.2fr) minmax(280px, 0.8fr);
        gap: 22px;
        align-items: stretch;
      }

      .screen-frame {
        overflow: hidden;
        border: 1px solid rgb(255 255 255 / 16%);
        border-radius: 8px;
        background: #171922;
        box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      }

      .screen-frame img {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        object-fit: cover;
        object-position: left top;
      }

      .screen-stack {
        display: grid;
        gap: 22px;
      }

      .workflow {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
        gap: 1px;
        background: #2d303a;
        border: 1px solid #2d303a;
      }

      .step {
        min-height: 230px;
        padding: 24px;
        background: #151720;
      }

      .step-number {
        display: inline-grid;
        place-items: center;
        width: 34px;
        height: 34px;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
        color: #0d0e12;
        background: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 820;
      }

      .step:nth-child(2) .step-number {
        background: var(--success);
      }

      .step:nth-child(3) .step-number {
        background: var(--warning);
      }

      .step:nth-child(4) .step-number {
        background: var(--paper);
      }

      .step h3 {
        margin: 0 0 12px;
        color: #ffffff;
        font-size: 22px;
      }

      .step p {
        margin: 0;
        color: rgb(255 255 255 / 66%);
        line-height: 1.48;
      }

      .guide-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
        gap: 16px;
      }

      .guide,
      .example-card {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        justify-content: space-between;
        min-height: 246px;
        padding: 24px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: 8px;
        background: var(--paper);
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      .guide:hover,
      .example-card:hover {
        border-color: #0d0e12;
        transform: translateY(-2px);
      }

      .guide-link {
        margin-top: 28px;
        font-weight: 780;
      }

      .code-strip {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.9fr) minmax(0, 1.1fr);
        gap: 24px;
        align-items: stretch;
      }

      pre {
        margin: 0;
        overflow: auto;
        min-height: 100%;
        padding: 24px;
        color: #f8fafc;
        background: #11131a;
        border: 1px solid #2d303a;
        border-radius: 8px;
        font-size: 13px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      code {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'SFMono-Regular', Consolas, monospace;
      }

      .example-card {
        color: #ffffff;
        background:
          linear-gradient(90deg, rgb(13 14 18 / 82%), rgb(13 14 18 / 42%)),
          var(--example-image) center / cover no-repeat;
        border-color: rgb(255 255 255 / 20%);
      }

      .example-card p {
        color: rgb(255 255 255 / 72%);
      }

      .footer {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 18px;
        padding: 34px clamp(20px, 5vw, 72px);
        color: rgb(255 255 255 / 62%);
        background: #0d0e12;
        border-top: 1px solid rgb(255 255 255 / 12%);
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      .footer a {
        color: #ffffff;
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      @media (max-width: 900px) {
        .site-nav {
          align-items: flex-start;
          flex-direction: column;
        }

        .nav-links {
          justify-content: flex-start;
        }

        .hero {
          min-height: 760px;
          background:
            linear-gradient(
              180deg,
              rgb(7 8 12 / 95%) 0%,
              rgb(7 8 12 / 76%) 58%,
              rgb(7 8 12 / 34%) 100%
            ),
            var(--hero-image) center / cover no-repeat;
        }

        .hero-metrics,
        .feature-grid,
        .workflow,
        .guide-grid,
        .screen-wall,
        .code-strip,
        .section-heading {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .screen-frame img {
          height: auto;
        }
      }

      @media (max-width: 560px) {
        .nav-links {
          gap: 12px;
        }

        .hero-content {
          padding-top: 70px;
          padding-bottom: 44px;
        }

        .hero {
          min-height: 66vh;
        }

        .hero-metrics {
          display: none;
        }

        h1 {
          font-size: clamp(56px, 18vw, 86px);
        }

        .hero-copy {
          font-size: 19px;
        }

        .section {
          padding-top: 62px;
          padding-bottom: 62px;
        }

        .feature,
        .guide,
        .example-card,
        .step {
          min-height: auto;
        }

        pre {
          overflow-x: hidden;
          white-space: pre-wrap;
          word-break: break-word;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <nav class="site-nav" aria-label="Rime Editor product navigation">
      <a class="brand" href="#top" aria-label="Rime Editor home">
        <span class="brand-word">Rime</span>
        <span class="brand-product">Editor</span>
      </a>
      <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="#workflow">Workflow</a>
        <a href="#inside">Inside the app</a>
        <a href="#guides">Guides</a>
        <a href="/rime-docs/get-started/what-is-rime/">CLI docs</a>
        <a class="nav-cta" href="https://github.com/danielsjoo/rime-editor">Repository</a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <main id="top">
      <section
        class="hero"
        aria-label="Rime Editor hero"
        style="--hero-image: url('/rime-docs/editor/assets/hero-dag-focus.jpg')"
      >
        <div class="hero-content">
          <div class="product-kicker">Desktop pipeline workbench</div>
          <h1>Rime Editor</h1>
          <p class="hero-copy">
            Shape data DAGs visually, inspect every table, edit scripts in place, and ship review
            reports from a focused desktop app built for Rime.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button primary" href="#inside">See the product</a>
            <a class="button" href="#guides">Explore guides</a>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-metrics" aria-label="Product highlights">
            <div class="metric">
              <strong>DAG first</strong><span>Canvas authoring with node-level feedback.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="metric">
              <strong>Data visible</strong
              ><span>Rows, columns, nulls, profiles, and previews.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="metric">
              <strong>Reports</strong><span>One-click review output for the current spec.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section tight" id="product">
        <div class="section-inner">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <h2>A product surface for Rime pipelines.</h2>
            <p class="lede">
              The CLI stays close to runtime execution. Rime Editor is the product layer for
              designing, debugging, and reviewing a pipeline when you need to see the data and graph
              at the same time.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-grid">
            <article class="feature">
              <div class="feature-topline"></div>
              <h3>Author the DAG without losing the YAML.</h3>
              <p>
                Drag through the pipeline, select nodes, and keep the current spec visible when you
                want the raw model.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="feature">
              <div class="feature-topline"></div>
              <h3>Make dataset scanning the front door.</h3>
              <p>
                Table previews lead with shape, null count, cardinality, column profiles, and
                sampled rows before code.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="feature">
              <div class="feature-topline"></div>
              <h3>Turn runs into reviewable evidence.</h3>
              <p>
                The report view renders the current pipeline with graph structure, table shapes,
                warnings, and outputs.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section dark" id="inside">
        <div class="section-inner">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <h2>Feels like an IDE for pipelines.</h2>
            <p class="lede">
              Visual graph, right-side inspector, data grid, script source, and report preview sit
              in one desktop workflow.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="screen-wall">
            <figure class="screen-frame">
              <img
                src="/rime-docs/editor/assets/table-scan-focus.jpg"
                alt="Focused Rime Editor table preview with scan metrics, column profiles, and sampled rows."
              />
            </figure>
            <div class="screen-stack">
              <figure class="screen-frame">
                <img
                  src="/rime-docs/editor/assets/report-dag-focus.jpg"
                  alt="Focused Rime report preview with DAG overview and output size tuples."
                />
              </figure>
              <figure class="screen-frame">
                <img
                  src="/rime-docs/editor/assets/yaml-spec-focus.jpg"
                  alt="Focused Rime Editor YAML spec view."
                />
              </figure>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section" id="workflow">
        <div class="section-inner">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <h2>From graph idea to reviewed run.</h2>
            <p class="lede">
              The editor is intentionally narrower than general docs. It explains the desktop
              workflow: open a project, inspect data, adjust nodes, and review output.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="workflow">
            <article class="step">
              <div class="step-number">1</div>
              <h3>Open a Rime project</h3>
              <p>Load the pipeline, see cached nodes, and orient around the canvas.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="step">
              <div class="step-number">2</div>
              <h3>Select and scan</h3>
              <p>
                Use the node panel to inspect table shape, columns, diffs, warnings, and source.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="step">
              <div class="step-number">3</div>
              <h3>Edit the spec</h3>
              <p>
                Move between visual controls, YAML, and script source without leaving the run
                context.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="step">
              <div class="step-number">4</div>
              <h3>Generate a report</h3>
              <p>Preview the current report in-app or open the generated file in a browser.</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section dark">
        <div class="section-inner">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <h2>The same DAG stays inspectable.</h2>
            <p class="lede">
              Rime Editor keeps the pipeline concrete: graph structure, YAML, table previews, SQL,
              and reports all point back to the same node ids.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="code-strip">
            <pre><code>nodes:
  - id: patient_lab_wide
    kind: sql
    in:
      patients_source: patients_source
      lab_agg: lab_agg
    source: queries/patient_lab_wide.sql

  - id: sql_cohort_refine
    kind: sql
    in:
      repeat_visitors: repeat_visitors
    source: queries/sql_cohort_refine.sql</code></pre>
            <a
              class="example-card"
              href="dag-showcase/"
              style="--example-image: url('/rime-docs/editor/assets/example-table-focus.jpg')"
            >
              <span>
                <h3>Example: dag-showcase</h3>
                <p>
                  A compact project that walks through CSV and Parquet sources, SQL nodes, derived
                  metrics, statistics, and report output.
                </p>
              </span>
              <span class="guide-link">Open example</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section" id="guides">
        <div class="section-inner">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <h2>Editor guides, separate from CLI docs.</h2>
            <p class="lede">
              These pages stay focused on the desktop product experience. Runtime concepts can stay
              in the Rime CLI documentation.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="guide-grid">
            <a class="guide" href="getting-started/">
              <span>
                <h3>Getting started</h3>
                <p>Open a project, run the DAG, and learn the main editor surfaces.</p>
              </span>
              <span class="guide-link">Read guide</span>
            </a>
            <a class="guide" href="dataset-scanning/">
              <span>
                <h3>Dataset scanning</h3>
                <p>
                  Use table metrics, column profiles, row samples, and diffs while selecting nodes.
                </p>
              </span>
              <span class="guide-link">Read guide</span>
            </a>
            <a class="guide" href="reports/">
              <span>
                <h3>Reports</h3>
                <p>
                  Preview the current report, inspect output sizes, and open the artifact in a
                  browser.
                </p>
              </span>
              <span class="guide-link">Read guide</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer">
      <span>Rime Editor product page</span>
      <span
        ><a href="/rime-docs/">Rime docs</a> /
        <a href="https://github.com/danielsjoo/rime-editor">Editor repository</a></span
      >
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
